content.problemStatement:
Alright, let’s dive into the very first Java program you’ll ever write: **Hello, World!**

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

- `public class HelloWorld`: This is like the name tag of your program. You’re telling the world, “Hey, I’m HelloWorld!”
- `public static void main(String[] args)`: This is the **main event**. It's the first place your program looks when it starts running. Imagine it like the front door to your program—if there's no door, no one can enter!
- `System.out.println("Hello, World!");`: This is the **shout-out**. You're telling the system, "Hey, world! Print this message!" It's like sending out a tweet to the universe!

As we continue through this course, we’ll discuss everything step by step. Don't worry if it seems like a lot right now, you'll get to know everything as we go along!

---


    Fun Fact:
    Did you know? Java is used in over 3 billion devices, ranging from computers to cars to smartphones! "

